14. RESPONSIBILITY
14.1 The Platform notifies the Data Subject that its Personal Data may be used to provide the
                        Tools, and in case of disagreement, the Data Subject must leave the Site and not use the
                        Platform Tools.
14.2 The Platform has the right to collect the Personal Data of the Data Subject to obtain
                        statistical data.
14.3 The Platform is not responsible for:
14.3.1 loss of Personal Data in the event of a hacker attack, hacking of the Site software,
                        illegal actions of third parties, illegal actions of the Client and actions that violate the
                        terms of the Privacy Policy;
14.3.2 provision by the Client of inaccurate information and Personal Data;
14.3.3 placement by the Client on the pages of the Blog of content that contains false
                        information and violates the intellectual property rights of third parties; which violates
                        dignity, religious beliefs, sexual orientation, and/or contains signs of racial discrimination
                        and/or violation of other third party rights.
14.4 We do not record videos, take screenshots or view the information that Users provide to the
                        Platform, except for viewing the video session, as requested by the Client.
14.5 We store the collected information, but only the Client who owns the Account can access it.
                        Plerdy does not use the data collected to distribute newsletters without your Consent.
14.6 Unfortunately, the transmission of information via the Internet may not be completely
                        secure. Although we make every effort to protect your Personal Data, we cannot guarantee the
                        secure process of transferring your Personal Data to our Site. In this regard, you are solely
                        responsible for possible failures in sharing your Personal Data with the Site. Upon receipt of
                        your Personal Data, we undertake the necessary technical and security measures to prevent
                        unauthorized access to your Personal Data.
14.7 If your Personal Data and other information is received using the survey tool system, the Client's Personal Data can be used for analysis purposes and the Client is personally responsible for the accuracy of the Personal Data and any other information transmitted by him/her
15. USE OF COOKIES AND LOCAL STORAGE
By Plerdy's commitment to privacy, transparency, and adherence to global data protection regulations, including the General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR), this section provides information about our use of browser local storage and, to clarify, our non-use of cookies.
15.1 Non-Use of Cookies: Plerdy does not use or set cookies in your browser. We respect your right to privacy and have chosen not to use cookies in any form or for any purpose on our websites, including a.plerdy.com. This means that we do not collect, store, or process any data through cookies nor allow third parties to do so on our behalf.
15.2 Use of Local Storage: Plerdy uses the Local Storage feature of your web browser to enhance your user experience and provide seamless services. This local storage allows us to store data such as user sessions, traffic channels, IP verification, form popup closing states, etc., on your device. This data is only used to enable key functionalities of our services and is not shared with any third parties or used for any other purpose.
15.3 Third-Party Analytics: Although Plerdy does not use cookies, we employ third-party analytics services, such as Google Analytics and Facebook, which may use cookies to collect data for analytics purposes. This data may include information about your visit to a.plerdy.com, such as the pages you view, the links you click, and other actions you take on the site. Please note that these third parties set these cookies by their own privacy policies, and Plerdy does not control their use or the data they collect.
15.4 Your Rights and Choices: You can control and limit local storage on your device. Most web browsers automatically accept local storage, but you can modify your browser's settings to decline local storage. Please note that if you choose to disable local storage, it may limit your use of certain features or functions on our website or service.
15.5 This policy applies to all users across all regions. Plerdy remains committed to respecting your privacy and complying with all applicable data protection laws and regulations.
16. ADULT POLICY
