17.1 The Platform has the right to change the Privacy Policy provisions to ensure the
                        preservation of Personal Data and in case of changes in the legislation governing the processing
                        of Personal Data.
17.2 The Platform notifies Clients of changes to the Privacy Policy by posting news on the Site.
                        Plerdy updates the date of changes to the current version of the Privacy Policy in the
                        "Last Update" line.
17.3 The Client is obliged to read the new terms of the Privacy Policy, and the Platform is not
                        responsible if the Client has not read the new terms of the Privacy Policy.
17.4 Electronic or otherwise retained copies of the Privacy Policy are considered genuine,
                        complete, valid, and enforceable versions of this Privacy Policy in effect when the Client
                        visits the Site. If the Client uses the Tools after updating the Privacy Policy, He agrees with
                        the new rules of Personal Data processing.
